com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.jfx.components.ImagePane
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class ImagePane extends javafx.scene.layout.AnchorPane

An extension of AnchorPane that displays an Image via an internally-wrapped ImageView.

    • requiresWritableContent

      public javafx.beans.property.BooleanProperty requiresWritableContentProperty

      A BooleanProperty defining whether this ImagePane is required to be writable or not.

      Details

      1. By default, ImagePanes are not required to be writable.
      2. Setting this ImagePane to Require Writable will cause an exception to be thrown if its content is ever changed to a non-writable Image type.
      3. Setting this ImagePane to Require Writable still allows its content to be null.

      Refer to the Universal Initialization Method for additional information.

  • Method Details

    • init

      void init​(@Nullable @Nullable Object input)

      Universal Initialization Method

      Initializes this ImagePane based on the specified input.

      Details

      1. The ImageView that is wrapped by this ImagePane is not Focus Traversable.
      2. The ImageView that is wrapped by this ImagePane is set to the same dimensions as this ImagePane object.
        1. Specifically, the anchors â€” Top, Bottom, Left, Right â€” are set to 0.
      3. Finally, the ImageView that is wrapped by this ImagePane is added as a child of this ImagePane.
      4. Use as Writable ImagePane: Refer to initWritableProperties().

      Parameter Details: Input

      1. Input Type
        1. Image: Used as the Image to construct the ImageView that is wrapped by this ImagePane.
        2. String: Used as the URL to construct the Image that is subsequently used to construct the ImageView that is wrapped by this ImagePane.
        3. null: The fallback option that results in the ImageView that is wrapped by this ImagePane to be empty.
      2. Throws an exception if the type of input passed to this method is not listed above.
      Parameters:
      input -
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - If the specified value is of an invalid type.

    • initWritableProperties

      private void initWritableProperties()

      Initializes properties that allow this ImagePane to be writable.

      Details

      1. To construct an ImagePane that must be writable, refer to requiresWritableContentProperty().
      2. If the Image displayed by this ImagePane is a WritableImage, the Writable Image Binding can be used to easily access it.
      3. If the Image displayed by this ImagePane is not a WritableImage, the WritableImage Binding will contain null.
      4. The Is Writable Binding is a convenience binding that reflects if the contents of this ImagePane are currently writable.
